[1762631]
Could you sum them up into a list and give a few explanations for each of them ? Thanks

Yes, of course.

AlphaBounce » The Map «

This is a fully detailed map of the AlphaBounce universe. It includes level information of space and surface. It contains also all known merchants, mission infomation, P- and K- capsules, antiradars, PID-pieces and other things. It is like moneymaker's Minemap, but the technology is much better.

Advice: This tool is not 100% done yet.

AlphaBounce » Global Map «

This is a very gobal look of the map. It contains simple information about merchants, P- and K- capsules. There are also information about missions that are scattered in the whole universe ("Star Dust", "Antimatter") Finally it provides a little tool to find the cheapest (known) shop for a specific item and a view of the current exploration of
» The Map «.

Temporary screenshot terminal

This is the backend for the » The Map «. You can add screenshot from ABScreenMaker without registration. The tool detects minerals, missiles and extra lives automatically and adds them instantly to
» The Map «.

Thank you very much !!!

OK, i have a few suggestions.

Please don't use ?x=0&y=0 in the link to the map. It is cookie based already and this parameters will overwrite the saved cookies. If no params are given the map will know, which point of space you viewed last time and will be centered to that point again. With params, you always will start on 0/0, that makes the cookie function obsolete.

Then, it is not called "Multi Map". I named it simply
» The Map «

You have forgotten the second tool completely. I mean the global map. Here is the description once again:

AlphaBounce » Global Map «

This is a very gobal look of the map. It contains simple information about merchants, P- and K- capsules. There are also information about missions that are scattered in the whole universe ("Star Dust", "Antimatter") Finally it provides a little tool to find the cheapest (known) shop for a specific item and a view of the current exploration of
» The Map «.

You can also add, that it shows the universe from -600 to 600 in BOTH directions.

(But the range of » The Map « is unlimited so far. [OK, its limit is a signed 16-bit integer ... ] )

Ka-rud! I've done this two days in a row now: if you're using ABScreenMaker, make sure you press alt before you press space. So anyway, I just rant like this to make sure it doesn't happen to others. Press alt before space. The missiles are whatever, but I'm just bummed that I missed out on uploading two more screens.

juberner: start the program, leave it somewhere opened, go to the game, enter a level, but don't switch to the program or anything, just press alt + space while you're in the game, before launching any of the balls. Then you can pause the game while you upload the images (or you can do that after you finish the level too). Just fill in the coordinates under the captured image and click submit. It will count the minerals for you and also open the upload page at the specified coordinates.

halasa: ABS works now with my FF4 too... not sure if it's because of the IE Tab 2 extension (because I didn't switch rendering engines, all tabs were FF, including the one with the game), but point is it works. Using FF 4.0.1 and ABScreenMaker v1.4.7
